1) Place slides in the "Slides" folder
2) Slides must be in the following format

[h](Content of header)
[1](Point 1)
[1.1](Subpoint of 1)
[2](Point 2)
[2.2](Subpoint of 2)
[2.2.2](Nested subpoint of 2)

When the script runs, it returns you an interactive shell.

After you are done with the shell, hit Ctrl-D

You will be given 3 choices:
1) Next slide
2) Prev slide
3) End the presentation
